==English==
===Etymology===
Pref. be- (for by) + time; that is, by the proper time. The -s is an adverbial  ending.

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /bɪ.taɪmzˈ/

===Adverb===
# In good season or time; before it is late; seasonably; early.
# In a short time; soon; speedily; forth with.

====Quotations====
<blockquote>
I was up betimes in the morning, but Holmes was afoot earlier
still, for I saw him as I dressed, coming up the drive.<BR>
&mdash;A. Conan Doyle in ''The Hound of the Baskervilles''
</blockquote>